about.description:
* polib allows you to manipulate, create, modify gettext files (pot, po and
  mo files). You can load existing files, iterate through it's entries,
  add, modify entries, comments or metadata, etc... or create new po files
  from scratch.

* polib supports out of the box any version of python ranging from 2.4 to
* latest 3.X version.

* polib is pretty stable now and is used by many opensource projects.
about.summary: A library to manipulate gettext files (po and mo files).

name: polib
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "polib" %}
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "fad87d13696127ffb27ea0882d6182f1a9cf8a5e2b37a587751166c51e5a332a" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 2
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - polib

about:
  home: http://bitbucket.org/izi/polib/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A library to manipulate gettext files (po and mo files).'
  description: |
    * polib allows you to manipulate, create, modify gettext files (pot, po and
      mo files). You can load existing files, iterate through it's entries,
      add, modify entries, comments or metadata, etc... or create new po files
      from scratch.

    * polib supports out of the box any version of python ranging from 2.4 to
    * latest 3.X version.

    * polib is pretty stable now and is used by many opensource projects.
  dev_url: https://bitbucket.org/izi/polib/wiki/Home
  doc_url: https://polib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
    
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - stuertz
